accessibility.text: go back to find your heart

At first, your head is full of the fear of dying, pain and hopelessness. It turns out that the more you struggle, the faster you'll sink into them. You can't tell how many marshes are there around you. They just gather around and don't leave even a corner for you.

Gradually, it seems that someone is taking your fear away. When the liquid is about to submerge your mouth, without any distraction from your mind, you finally make it out and run away from the liquid creatures as far as possible, exerting all your strength.
There appears a bridge, right in front of you. You are not surprised at all. In other words, you have already lost sadness, joy, and fear.
